260
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:06,519
You brat. How dare you talk like that?

261
00:17:06,519 --> 00:17:07,820
Who let you come here?

262
00:17:07,820 --> 00:17:09,079
What's going on?

263
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:10,599
- It's alright.
- I should ask you that question.

264
00:17:10,599 --> 00:17:11,680
And you're asking me?

265
00:17:12,239 --> 00:17:13,540
You're really something.

266
00:17:13,540 --> 00:17:15,319
Just because he's not your own,
you can just boss him around?

267
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:18,400
Don't talk to my mom like that.

268
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:20,000
This little girl.

269
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:21,919
Please leave.

270
00:17:21,919 --> 00:17:23,199
You're not welcome here.

271
00:17:25,239 --> 00:17:26,439
Neither are you.

272
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:29,319
Come out with me.

273
00:17:29,319 --> 00:17:30,880
I have work to do.

274
00:17:42,199 --> 00:17:44,760
If you don't make things clear to me today,

275
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:48,239
I'll get an excavator
to tear down this house tomorrow.

276
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,119
Talk nicely with your dad.

277
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:01,079
I'm sorry, Uncle.

278
00:18:01,079 --> 00:18:02,240
It's okay.

279
00:18:24,199 --> 00:18:26,880
So you're living here with Su Yu?

280
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:34,760
If you don't want to live at home, fine.

281
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:37,319
I bought you that apartment at Guomao.

282
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:41,079
But instead of staying in that nice apartment,

283
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:43,160
every now and then,

284
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,760
you come to this dump to suffer.

285
00:18:46,079 --> 00:18:47,299
Isn't this a slap in my face?

286
00:18:47,299 --> 00:18:48,800
How did I slap your face?

287
00:18:49,959 --> 00:18:52,460
What do you think I'm working so hard for?

288
00:18:52,460 --> 00:18:54,560
Why do I make so much money?

289
00:18:55,479 --> 00:18:56,520
Your way of life

290
00:18:57,560 --> 00:18:59,079
is trampling on my labor.

291
00:18:59,079 --> 00:19:00,640
I didn't ask for your labor.

292
00:19:01,599 --> 00:19:02,600
Don't… don't be angry.

293
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:05,119
At least this means they are getting along.

294
00:19:05,119 --> 00:19:06,319
We still have a chance in the future.

295
00:19:06,319 --> 00:19:07,599
You're his mother.

296
00:19:07,599 --> 00:19:08,959
We're a family.

297
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:13,140
He glares and growls at you,

298
00:19:13,140 --> 00:19:14,160
but he runs to your ex-husband…

299
00:19:17,119 --> 00:19:19,880
He runs to other people
and does hard labor smiling.

300
00:19:25,479 --> 00:19:26,640
I just don't get it.

301
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,800
What are you playing?

302
00:19:30,199 --> 00:19:31,880
I just like their family.

303
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:33,560
I like their home, their atmosphere.

304
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:35,040
Is there a problem?

305
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:36,359
Is there something wrong with your brain?

306
00:19:36,359 --> 00:19:38,199
How did I raise a son like you?

307
00:19:38,199 --> 00:19:40,120
So you can steal other people's wives,

308
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:42,040
but I can't be a son to others?

309
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,719
Why should you get all the benefits?

310
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,080
Don't get angry.

311
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:54,580
- Hit me.
- Don't hit him. Don't.

312
00:19:54,580 --> 00:19:55,800
Get out of my way.

313
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,536
Are you okay?

314
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:12,800
Are you alright?

315
00:20:13,479 --> 00:20:16,239
I'm fine. I'll apply some medicine
when we get back.

316
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:25,279
<i>Your way of life is trampling on my labor.</i>

317
00:20:25,279 --> 00:20:27,040
<i>I didn't ask for your labor.</i>

318
00:20:36,079 --> 00:20:37,119
Don't overthink it.

319
00:20:38,479 --> 00:20:40,000
He's just a kid.

320
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,880
He's just trying to make you angry.

321
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:44,079
To get your attention.

322
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,359
Do you believe what he says
about liking that family?

323
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:50,640
I know exactly what Su Yu's dad is like.

324
00:20:51,479 --> 00:20:52,680
There's no way he looks up to him.

325
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,839
Alright, don't get angry.

326
00:21:00,719 --> 00:21:02,199
What does he really want?

327
00:21:35,959 --> 00:21:37,839
Usually, you're so arrogant.

328
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:39,599
But now you're awfully quiet.

329
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:43,119
My dad made such a scene this afternoon,

330
00:21:44,079 --> 00:21:45,959
and I felt quite sorry for Uncle.

331
00:21:50,368 --> 00:21:51,439
It's nothing.

332
00:21:52,599 --> 00:21:53,959
My mom started it, didn't she?

333
00:21:55,584 --> 00:21:56,760
Stop mulling over it.

334
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:58,880
My dad is a broad-minded person.

335
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:02,479
Why are you so okay with this?

336
00:22:03,079 --> 00:22:05,359
Normally, you would be
emotional about these things.

337
00:22:14,359 --> 00:22:15,839
Actually, you have quite an influence on me.

338
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,104
What influence?

339
00:22:22,119 --> 00:22:23,136
Values.

340
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:27,120
What kind of influence can a person like me

341
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:29,220
have on a straight-A student like you
in terms of values?

342
00:22:29,220 --> 00:22:30,272
What do you think?

343
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:32,319
Why do you think I became your friend?

344
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:35,099
It must be because
you have qualities that I don't,

345
00:22:35,099 --> 00:22:36,640
and I can learn from you.

346
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:38,912
What qualities?

347
00:22:42,760 --> 00:22:43,880
To tell you the truth,

348
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:46,119
before I met you,

349
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:50,199
my concept of money was somewhat extreme.

350
00:22:51,760 --> 00:22:52,760
I always felt that my parents

351
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:54,339
shouldn't have planted

352
00:22:54,339 --> 00:22:55,719
the idea of poverty in my mind,

353
00:22:57,920 --> 00:23:00,599
making me desperately use self-improvement
to cover up my inner inferiority.

354
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:06,680
After knowing you,

355
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:09,640
I gradually realized

356
00:23:11,319 --> 00:23:13,599
that wealth and poverty
are not a gap between us.

357
00:23:15,479 --> 00:23:17,599
It's just an objective fact about our parents.

358
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:22,000
What you have, you may not enjoy,

359
00:23:23,328 --> 00:23:24,480
and what I lack

360
00:23:25,199 --> 00:23:26,599
does not mean deprivation.

361
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:34,880
You're absolutely right.

362
00:23:35,959 --> 00:23:37,320
The ability to make money

363
00:23:37,320 --> 00:23:39,359
is an objective fact about our parents.

364
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:42,976
Love, however,

365
00:23:44,079 --> 00:23:45,439
is a subjective consciousness.

366
00:23:49,959 --> 00:23:51,008
Although,

367
00:23:53,560 --> 00:23:55,199
I do think your dad loves you.

368
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,479
Today, when you were working on the roof,

369
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:05,079
I saw the look in your dad's eyes.

370
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:06,880
He was distressed.

371
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:11,079
Have you ever thought

372
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:16,760
that maybe your mom's incident
was really an accident?

373
00:24:18,359 --> 00:24:20,959
Of course, I'm not making excuses for anyone.

374
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:22,560
I just think

375
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:26,040
the thorn between the two of you

376
00:24:26,920 --> 00:24:28,199
should be removed.

377
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:37,079
I'm afraid to touch this matter.

378
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:41,920
Every single detail

379
00:24:43,079 --> 00:24:44,160
about the scene

380
00:24:45,239 --> 00:24:46,280
of my mom's accident

381
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:51,640
makes me shudder.

382
00:25:13,359 --> 00:25:14,400
You're not really upset

383
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,079
about what happened today, right?

384
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:21,359
Or what? I should be like you?

385
00:25:21,359 --> 00:25:22,640
Act as if nothing happened?

386
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,719
That's how Xiao San is.

387
00:25:27,239 --> 00:25:28,599
She speaks rudely,

388
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:32,760
but she doesn't mean any harm.

389
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:38,400
I don't think she was wrong.

390
00:25:39,680 --> 00:25:41,359
I think we should reflect on that.

391
00:25:41,959 --> 00:25:42,976
Reflect?

392
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:45,680
How to reflect?

393
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:48,319
Reflect on why Su Yu is living like this.

394
00:25:49,199 --> 00:25:50,400
I married you

395
00:25:50,959 --> 00:25:53,880
wanting our two families to have a better life.

396
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:56,479
But looking at it now,

397
00:25:56,479 --> 00:25:59,199
Su Yu's life has not improved.

398
00:26:00,599 --> 00:26:02,680
That's because you're asking too much.

399
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:04,680
You're doing really well now.

400
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:06,119
Every day, he wears

401
00:26:06,119 --> 00:26:07,380
clean clothes,

402
00:26:07,380 --> 00:26:09,060
and eats a hot meal.

403
00:26:09,060 --> 00:26:10,239
Compared with the past…

404
00:26:10,239 --> 00:26:12,400
Your bar is too low.

405
00:26:13,599 --> 00:26:16,800
We can't just slack off

406
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:18,680
just because he is understanding.

407
00:26:20,719 --> 00:26:22,440
Su Yu and Duo,

408
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:25,000
they both grew up in single-parent families.

409
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:27,740
We already owe them in this aspect.

410
00:26:27,740 --> 00:26:29,800
If we cannot

411
00:26:30,479 --> 00:26:31,740
satisfy them materially,

412
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:34,359
what value do we have as parents?

413
00:26:35,712 --> 00:26:36,800
You're right.

414
00:26:37,439 --> 00:26:39,079
I'll go get a part-time job tomorrow.

415
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:41,000
It's not about getting a part-time job.

416
00:26:41,880 --> 00:26:43,439
We need to change our mindset.

417
00:26:44,768 --> 00:26:45,780
What do you mean?

418
00:26:45,780 --> 00:26:47,239
Here's what I think.

419
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:49,500
Look at us now,

420
00:26:49,500 --> 00:26:51,880
working our asses off
and getting paid so little,

421
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:54,400
barely enough for basic living expenses.

422
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:56,539
If you get a part-time job,

423
00:26:56,539 --> 00:26:58,959
all you can do is physical work.

424
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:01,139
And the factory where you work,

425
00:27:01,139 --> 00:27:02,199
it's been here for over twenty years, right?

426
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:05,040
The workload is heavy and gets you dirty.

427
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:06,380
And there's no insurance.

428
00:27:06,380 --> 00:27:07,800
With your physique,

429
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:09,680
how long can you work there?

430
00:27:11,319 --> 00:27:13,439
But at my age,

431
00:27:13,439 --> 00:27:14,839
if I go find a job again…

432
00:27:14,839 --> 00:27:16,900
Who told you to find a job?

433
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:18,040
Let's do it ourselves.

434
00:27:18,599 --> 00:27:19,648
Do it ourselves?

435
00:27:20,239 --> 00:27:21,360
How?

436
00:27:21,360 --> 00:27:22,959
Look at my small shop now,

437
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:25,720
the foot traffic is small.

438
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:27,560
And if it gets busy, I can't cope.

439
00:27:29,599 --> 00:27:32,240
If we borrow some money
from relatives and friends,

440
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,380
rent a store,

441
00:27:33,380 --> 00:27:34,599
and we can manage it together.

442
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:37,680
That way, I don't have to hide
from the city management every day,

443
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:39,520
and the customer flow will be bigger.

444
00:27:40,359 --> 00:27:42,740
The food will be clean and hygienic,

445
00:27:42,740 --> 00:27:44,199
and we can raise the prices a bit.

446
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:47,839
Opening a shop?

447
00:27:53,760 --> 00:27:55,760
That's not a small matter.

448
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:01,020
Do you know why I took to your dad

449
00:28:01,020 --> 00:28:02,079
like a duck to water?

450
00:28:04,599 --> 00:28:05,640
I have no idea.

451
00:28:06,800 --> 00:28:08,560
You two are from two
completely different worlds.

452
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:12,280
Because of his approval of you.

453
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:16,100
No matter what you do,

454
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:17,440
even if it's something small,

455
00:28:17,440 --> 00:28:19,119
your dad always praises you endlessly.

456
00:28:20,839 --> 00:28:21,880
That's something

457
00:28:22,719 --> 00:28:24,439
I've never had.

458
00:28:27,040 --> 00:28:28,959
Maybe your dad is just not good at expression.

459
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:32,832
No.

460
00:28:34,479 --> 00:28:36,119
Actually, my physical condition is very good.

461
00:28:37,079 --> 00:28:39,719
I won the youth wrestling championship
when I was young,

462
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:42,920
and was rated as a national
second-level athlete in middle school.

463
00:28:43,560 --> 00:28:45,880
But these were not important to my dad.

464
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:49,520
Compared to my body, he values my mind more.

465
00:28:50,040 --> 00:28:51,239
He planned all my future

466
00:28:51,239 --> 00:28:53,280
in his business blueprint.

467
00:28:54,599 --> 00:28:55,760
The rest of my highlights,

468
00:28:58,359 --> 00:28:59,439
it's like they don't exist.

469
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:03,479
So, what is your dream?

470
00:29:05,800 --> 00:29:07,000
I want to be an astronaut.

471
00:29:08,400 --> 00:29:09,719
Does it sound crazy?

472
00:29:10,688 --> 00:29:11,712
Not at all.

473
00:29:12,280 --> 00:29:13,920
With your physical condition,

474
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:15,199
if you work on your academic courses,

475
00:29:15,839 --> 00:29:16,920
you can definitely get in.

476
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:18,940
Really?

477
00:29:18,940 --> 00:29:20,064
Of course.

478
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:25,560
Tell me, which star do you like?

479
00:29:26,239 --> 00:29:27,296
Your big brother will give it to you.

480
00:29:28,359 --> 00:29:29,359
You're my 'little brother'.

481
00:29:30,160 --> 00:29:31,199
Not again.

482
00:29:37,199 --> 00:29:38,208
So…

483
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,160
What is your dream?

484
00:29:41,408 --> 00:29:42,464
Guess.

485
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:45,920
Scientist?

486
00:29:47,239 --> 00:29:48,280
You think I'm in kindergarten?

487
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:51,380
It's naive for others to have that dream,

488
00:29:51,380 --> 00:29:52,740
but it's blasphemy to your brain

489
00:29:52,740 --> 00:29:54,680
if you don't want to be a scientist.

490
00:29:58,400 --> 00:30:00,800
So, what is it really?

491
00:30:04,079 --> 00:30:06,439
I want to be a traveler, an adventurer.

492
00:30:07,959 --> 00:30:09,599
Traveler?

493
00:30:10,319 --> 00:30:11,360
Yes.

494
00:30:12,760 --> 00:30:15,199
I want to see the prairies and the sea.

495
00:30:15,959 --> 00:30:17,680
I want to explore mountains, rivers, and lakes.

496
00:30:22,319 --> 00:30:23,392
So, where

497
00:30:24,599 --> 00:30:25,680
do you want to go the most?

498
00:30:29,359 --> 00:30:30,432
Tibet.

499
00:30:37,920 --> 00:30:40,160
Brother, I can't sleep.

500
00:30:40,160 --> 00:30:42,040
I want to hear a story.

501
00:30:43,328 --> 00:30:44,448
Okay.

502
00:30:45,199 --> 00:30:46,959
I want to hear it too.

503
00:30:49,439 --> 00:30:50,624
Wait for me.

504
00:30:59,392 --> 00:31:00,439
What do you want to hear?

505
00:31:00,439 --> 00:31:01,504
Ghost Blows Out the Light.

506
00:31:05,479 --> 00:31:07,740
Ghost Blows Out the Light again?
You love it so much.

507
00:31:07,740 --> 00:31:09,520
Come on, lie down, and let's start.

508
00:31:17,119 --> 00:31:19,020
We had just walked behind the sand dune

509
00:31:19,020 --> 00:31:20,959
when Ye Yixin stepped into a void,

510
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:23,439
and her whole body sank halfway.

511
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,359
I quickly grabbed her

512
00:31:26,119 --> 00:31:28,199
and blew the whistle for help.

513
00:31:29,040 --> 00:31:30,439
But it doesn't seem to be quicksand.

514
00:31:31,160 --> 00:31:33,640
Quicksand has a strong pull
and swallows things quickly.

515
00:31:34,160 --> 00:31:35,359
If it were really quicksand,

516
00:31:35,959 --> 00:31:37,959
I wouldn't be able to hold her
with my strength.

517
00:31:38,880 --> 00:31:40,620
And after she sank halfway down,

518
00:31:40,620 --> 00:31:41,760
it stopped.

519
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:44,760
It seems like the bottom is solid.

520
00:32:03,874 --> 00:32:08,386
<i>♫ Mila, Mila ♫</i>

521
00:32:11,170 --> 00:32:15,146
<i>♫ You're such a beautiful flower ♫</i>

522
00:32:17,602 --> 00:32:22,018
<i>♫ Mila, Mila ♫</i>

523
00:32:24,834 --> 00:32:28,706
<i>♫ You're the summer I can't bear to part with ♫</i>

524
00:32:31,732 --> 00:32:35,864
<i>♫ You always have so many ideas ♫</i>

525
00:32:38,626 --> 00:32:42,882
<i>♫ Occasionally, you're not so obedient ♫</i>

526
00:32:45,534 --> 00:32:49,666
<i>♫ But it's you who bring the worries ♫</i>

527
00:32:52,322 --> 00:32:56,853
<i>♫ That make a complete family ♫</i>

528
00:32:57,890 --> 00:33:00,482
<i>♫ From today, every minute and second ♫</i>

529
00:33:00,482 --> 00:33:04,322
<i>♫ Will be the treasure of my life ♫</i>

530
00:33:05,570 --> 00:33:07,330
<i>♫ Because with you by my side ♫</i>

531
00:33:07,330 --> 00:33:10,146
<i>♫ Everything becomes beautiful ♫</i>

532
00:33:11,618 --> 00:33:14,146
<i>♫ From today, every moment and instant ♫</i>

533
00:33:14,146 --> 00:33:18,050
<i>♫ Will be the happiest time in life ♫</i>

534
00:33:19,298 --> 00:33:23,298
<i>♫ No matter where you are, home will be ♫</i>

535
00:33:24,450 --> 00:33:27,554
<i>♫ In that place ♫</i>

536
00:33:34,466 --> 00:33:38,018
<i>♫ In that place ♫</i>

537
00:33:56,834 --> 00:34:01,090
<i>♫ In that place ♫</i>
